ğŸ—‚ï¸ 4. Component-wise Explanation (Overview)

We will expand each of these in the next step:

Component	Responsibility
StudentApp - Parent container, coordinates child components
StudentForm -	Create new student records
StudentList -	Display students with search, sort, pagination, edit, delete
StudentDashboard - Display total students and class-wise counts
StudentChart - Visual representation of student distribution

ğŸ”„ 5. Data Flow Summary

User creates a student via StudentForm
StudentForm calls Apex to insert record
StudentForm fires a custom event
Parent component listens to event
Parent triggers refresh on StudentList
StudentList refreshes data using refreshApex
Dashboard and Chart update automatically via @wire

ğŸ“˜ 6. Apex Controller â€“ Detailed Explanation
Apex Class Name:
StudentController

Purpose:
Handles all server-side operations for the Student Management App.
Provides reusable methods that are consumed by multiple LWC components.

Apex Methods Used:
1ï¸âƒ£ getAllStudents()
@AuraEnabled(cacheable=true)
public static List<Student__c> getAllStudents() {
    return [
        SELECT Id, Name, Email__c, Class__c, Phone__c 
        FROM Student__c
    ];
}


Why it is important:
Used by StudentList, StudentDashboard, and StudentChart
cacheable=true enables:
Better performance
Use with @wire

Manual refresh using refreshApex:

2ï¸âƒ£ createStudent(Student__c student)
@AuraEnabled
public static Student__c createStudent(Student__c student) {
    insert student;
    return student;
}

Purpose:
Inserts new student records from StudentForm
Returns inserted record for confirmation

3ï¸âƒ£ updateStudent(Student__c student)
@AuraEnabled
public static void updateStudent(Student__c student) {
    update student;
}


Purpose:
Updates student details from Edit Modal
Used by StudentList

4ï¸âƒ£ deleteStudent(Id studentId)
@AuraEnabled
public static void deleteStudent(Id studentId) {
    delete [SELECT Id FROM Student__c WHERE Id = :studentId];
}


Purpose:
Deletes student records from the datatable
Triggers UI refresh using refreshApex

âœ… Apex Design Highlights
Single controller reused across components
Clean separation of backend and UI
Optimized queries
Supports reactive UI updates

