7. Lightning Web Components â€“ Detailed Flow
StudentApp (Parent Component)

Responsibility:
Acts as container
Coordinates communication between child components

Key Functionality:
Listens to studentcreated event from StudentForm
Calls refreshList() on StudentList
StudentForm (Create Student)

Responsibilities:
Accepts user input
Builds student object
Calls Apex create method
Fires custom event to parent

Key Concepts Used:
Event handling
Custom events
Toast notifications
Input binding

StudentList (Core Component)

Responsibilities:
Display students in datatable

Handle:
Search
Sorting
Pagination
Edit
Delete

Key Concepts Used:
lightning-datatable
Row actions
Edit modal
Integrated logic using applyAll()
refreshApex
StudentDashboard

Responsibilities:
Display summary cards:
Total Students
Class A, B, C counts

Key Concepts Used:
@wire
Client-side aggregation
Reactive UI updates
StudentChart

Responsibilities:
Display pie chart of student distribution

Key Concepts Used:
Static Resources
Chart.js integration
renderedCallback
lwc:dom="manual"
Dynamic chart updates

ğŸ“˜ 8. Key LWC Concepts Demonstrated

@wire and refreshApex
Parent-child communication
Custom events
Reactive state management
Datatable advanced features
Lifecycle hooks
External JS integration
Modular architecture

